PUH-BrianMartell The Observability Lemma states that the ripple field ϕ(x,t) and its time derivative ∂_t ϕ on any spacelike hypersurface (Cauchy surface) uniquely determine the full solution everywhere — a standard result for hyperbolic PDEs like the linear ripple equation. Simple picture: •  At a fixed time t=0, know ϕ(x,0) and ∂_t ϕ(x,0) everywhere. •  These Cauchy data “launch” the wave in both directions. •  Uniqueness theorem: only one solution matches this data. •  Result: present ripple field (value + velocity) determines past and future. Rigorous proof uses energy method: •  Assume two solutions with same Cauchy data → difference ψ = 0 on surface. •  Energy E(t) = ∫ (∂_t ψ)^2 + T (∇ψ)^2 d³x conserved. •  E(0) = 0 → E(t) = 0 everywhere → ψ = 0. •  Thus unique solution. This proves observability — ripple data determine full state.
